deck: Noam is an openly young gay men who met Anole online. They started dating soon after.
description:
Story

Noam met Anole online. They started chatting and were both into each other. Noam knew Victor was a mutant but never saw a picture of him. Still he agreed to go on a date with him but Victor never showed up, because he was afraid of Noam's reaction of his look.

Later, Victor found Noam sitting at the Washington Square Park and finally revealed himself to him. He asked Noam if he still wanted to date him and Noam didn't hesitated at all. He said he will took him to the next coffee shop and graped Victors hand while they walked side by side.
name: Noam

deck: Amalia is one of the main characters of Heaven Sent Gaming's Reverie.
description: Amalia is one of the main characters in the Heaven Sent Gaming webcomic strip Reverie. Personality-wise she is nervy, hard working, witty, and ambitious. Her most impressive ability is her capability to master any task, she is a jack of all trades that's able to quickly master any skill. Though she is just a kid, she likes to work multiple jobs; her main job is as a crew member at a local fast food restaurant, Fries n' Stuff. She is currently in a relationship with Bronjay.
name: Amalia

volume_credits.name: Limited Edition Collector's Omnibus of Heaven Sent Gaming's First 2 Years Of Comics And Novels

deck: Bronjay is one of the main characters of Heaven Sent Gaming's Reverie.
description: Bronjay is one of the main characters in the Heaven Sent Gaming webcomic strip Reverie. Personality-wise he is loyal, chivalrous, and creative. He is an extremely well-meaning kid, that mostly keeps to himself, but he has a rampant daydreaming imagination which leads him to get into trouble. He is currently in a relationship with Amalia.
name: Bronjay

volume_credits.name: Limited Edition Collector's Omnibus of Heaven Sent Gaming's First 2 Years Of Comics And Novels

deck: Bronwen is one of the main characters of Heaven Sent Gaming's Reverie.
description: Bronwen is one of the main characters in the Heaven Sent Gaming webcomic strip Reverie. Personality-wise he is inteligent, cunning, and resourceful. His most impressive ability is his hyper-intelligence, he is beyond a genius, and has been shown to be able to build a time-space manipulator from items in his standard bedroom. He is the younger brother of Bronjay, and the youngest of the Bron family.
name: Bronwen

volume_credits.name: Limited Edition Collector's Omnibus of Heaven Sent Gaming's First 2 Years Of Comics And Novels

description: Hoopes is one of the main characters in the Heaven Sent Gaming webcomic strip Reverie. Personality-wise he is chivalrous, patient, and loyal. He is an extremely well-meaning kid, that mostly keeps to himself, but he has a rampant daydreaming imagination which leads him to get into trouble. Unlike his best-pal Bronjay, he has a wide variety of hobbies, including music, arts, and the sciences.

Unlike her best-pal Amalia, she does not like working but instead very into volunteering and joining clubs. She has a rampant imagination, and much like Bronjay it can get her into trouble.

deck: Sepie is one of the main characters of Heaven Sent Gaming's Reverie.
description: Sepie is one of the main characters in the Heaven Sent Gaming webcomic strip Reverie. Personality-wise he is nervy, brave, and loyal. He is a floating squid, and is the pet of the Bron family, though his relationship to the family has never been stated. He has saved Bronjay and Bronwen from various things, even defeating a Mech Sepie, that Bronwen built, after it attempted to attack its creator.
name: Sepie
